gomodel:SYNGO_738  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: The paper examines the sub cellular localization of GlyT2 in rat brainstem and spinal cord tissue using immunogold labelling for electron microscopy, sub cellular fractionation and immunoisolation of synaptic membranes.\n\nThe authors have generated a new antibody for GlyT2:'The novel antibody\nrecognized a single band of the expected size in brain tissue (90 kDa) and the staining was largely displaced by the Nt-GLYT2-Glutathion-S-transferase (Nt-\nGLYT2-GST) fusion protein that was used as antigen'.\n\nFigure 1-Electron microscopy of double peroxidase and gold-particle immunolabeling performed on ventral horn of spinal cord tissue (1a) or brainstem tissue (ab). Immunogold labeling of Glyt2 is seen in the synaptic plasma membrane and in the presynaptic compartment.\n\nFigure 2 - sub cellular fractionation of brainstem tissue. Strong GlyT2 labeling is seen in the synaptosomal P2 fraction, in the plasma membrane LP1 fraction, and in the synaptic vesicle membrane LP2 fractions. The LP2 fraction was further isolated on a Glycerol gradient to separate vesicles of different sizes. Strong signal for GlyT2 was seen in the fractions 11 and 12, which include plasma membrane proteins and is not enriched for synaptic vesicle proteins.\n\nFigure 5b shows a robust immunostaining signal for GlyT2 on the plasma membrane of brainstem neurons in culture.\n\n1/7/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Rats (Wistar strain) were deeply anesthetized with pentobarbital\n(100 mg/kg) and perfused through the left ventricle-aorta with a fixative\nsolution of paraformaldehyde 4% in 0.1 M sodium phosphate pH 7.4,\npreceded by a brief flush (10-15 seconds) of 0.1 M sodium phosphate\npH 7.4 without fixative." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
